98
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:54,0000
well, they didn't have a B plan.

99
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,0000
They just capitulated.

100
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:05,0000
But you acted at that point as if you had some plan.

101
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:12,0000
You even publicly, now comes the friendly aggressive part, acted as if...

102
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,0000
I remember a couple of interviews, no?

103
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:19,0000
As if in a couple of days you will see, I will make a deal and so on and so on.

104
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:22,0000
So, what is your vision?

105
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:29,0000
Did you really have in your mind what, but not in Tony Blair sense, a third way?

106
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:34,0000
You know, like, was there possible to break out of this vicious cycle,

107
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:40,0000
either compromise with European Union or Grexit, simple, brutal Grexit,

108
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:45,0000
which you convinced me once we talked when you were finance minister,

109
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:51,0000
and you told me that some financial specialist told you that if you do brutally Grexit,

110
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:55,0000
the standard of living would have fallen for a further 30%,

111
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,0000
that it would have been a catastrophe.

112
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:02,0000
What was your third way, if there was any?

113
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:07,0000
I mean it seriously, because many people think that you didn't have a third way,

114
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,0000
that you were also bluffing.

115
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:16,0000
There was a plan, I still believe that it was eminently workable and...

116
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,0000
You still believe it?

117
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:20,0000
I still believe it, I know it. And you know why?

118
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:23,0000
Because I was told so by my enemies.

119
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,0000
I only believe my enemies, I never believe my friends,

120
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:30,0000
not because they are not trustworthy people, but usually they don't know.

121
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,0000
They know as much as I know, which is not that much.

122
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,0000
Who are they? Name them.

123
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:41,0000
Mario Draghi, the president of the European Central Bank.

124
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,0000
What was the plan?

125
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:47,0000
The plan had... I'm not going to speak too long about this,

126
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:50,0000
because I've written a whole book about it.

127
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,0000
Because you don't really have a plan, no?

128
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:56,0000
No, no, I did have a plan, it's just I've spoken about it far too often.

129
00:10:56,000 --> 00:11:02,0000
And there is a 600 page book on it. But, OK, what was the plan?

130
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:07,0000
The plan, by the way, Slavoj, was the reason why I was finance minister.

131
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:11,0000
Because I was not a member of the Syriza party, I never wanted to be a minister,

132
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:14,0000
I didn't want to be a parliamentarian or a politician for that matter.

133
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:18,0000
It's just because when Tsipras was about to become prime minister,

134
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:21,0000
I said to him, "So what are you going to do when they squeeze you?"

135
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:24,0000
And he said, "I have no idea. Do you have an idea?"

136
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:27,0000
So I had an idea and I proposed to him the plan.

137
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:30,0000
And he said, "This is great, but I don't have anybody to implement it.

138
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,0000
You're going to have to be finance minister."

139
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,0000
And I thought, "Oh, shit, I should have kept my mouth shut."

140
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:40,0000
But then, of course, moral duty, all those bourgeois concepts, right?

141
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:44,0000
Pushed me to say yes. But what was the plan? The plan was this.

142
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:49,0000
This is the beginning of 2015.

143
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:57,0000
Draghi, who was in the central bank since the end of 2011,

144
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:01,0000
spent all the time between 2011 and the beginning of 2015

145
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:06,0000
struggling to create the circumstances for him to buy Italian debt

146
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:08,0000
because Italy was on the way out.

147
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:11,0000
3 trillion euros worth of debt.

148
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,0000
If that debt had blown up, the Eurozone would have blown up.

149
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,0000
You wouldn't have euros in your pockets now.

150
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,0000
Germany would have recreated the Deutsche Marker. It's very simple.

151
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:26,0000
So the only thing that saved the euro was that he was going to save

152
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:30,0000
the Italian state. But he had to go against the German central bank.

153
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:34,0000
So there was a big clash between Mario Draghi, the European central bank,

154
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:38,0000
and Jens Weidmann, the head of the Bundesbank, the German central bank.

155
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,0000
They even ended up in court.

156
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:49,0000
The German central bank chief tabled 120 pages of an affidavit

157
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:53,0000
against Mario Draghi in the European courts.

158
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:56,0000
It was a huge clash.

159
00:12:56,000 --> 00:13:01,0000
So Merkel and Draghi were working against the chief of the Bundesbank.

160
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,0000
We're talking about serious clashes now.

161
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:07,0000
These are the contradictions of the system, that if you're a tiny little

162
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:11,0000
pipsqueak finance minister of a tiny pipsqueak country, you have to exploit.

163
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:22,0000
And I thought I had found the weak point of the empire, of the Star Wars spaceship.

164
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:29,0000
And it was this. The only way Draghi managed to convince the European courts

165
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:35,0000
to allow him to buy Italian debt was if he pledged that he wouldn't allow

166
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:40,0000
one euro of the debt that he purchased to be written down.

167
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:47,0000
Sorry, so that people understand, what do you mean by written down?

168
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:53,0000
Written off. Wiped out. Expunged. Haircut.

169
00:13:53,000 --> 00:14:00,0000
The Greek state owed 29 billion to the central bank.

170
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:03,0000
These were bonds that the central bank had.

171
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:07,0000
And they were in Greek law, which meant the finance minister of Greece

172
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,0000
could simply do whatever he wanted with them.

173
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:12,0000
Say that it would not be paid for another 100 years.

174
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:16,0000
This is effectively writing it down.

175
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:23,0000
So, a week before the election, I knew we were going to win.

176
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:26,0000
It was clear from the polls.

177
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:32,0000
In an interview with the BBC, I was just a candidate for a member of parliament,

178
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:37,0000
formally, right? But I knew I was going to be finance minister if we won.

179
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:41,0000
In an interview with the BBC, I was asked some irrelevant question,

180
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:48,0000
and on purpose I said I gave an irrelevant answer as a signal to Mario Draghi.

181
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:53,0000
And it was this. If Syriza wins, and we're in government,

182
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:57,0000
immediately we're going to get a phone call from Frankfurt,

183
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:02,0000
from the European Central Bank, threatening us with bank closures and squeezing.

184
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:08,0000
The answer should be we're going to write down those 29 billion of debt.

185
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:12,0000
Because this is what you do. When your central bank squeezes you,

186
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:18,0000
you squeeze them back. And that would impede the purchase of Italian debt.

187
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:24,0000
Cut. Two weeks later, I'm finance minister, and I'm in Frankfurt,

188
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,0000
and I have my first meeting with Mario Draghi.

189
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:33,0000
First thing he says to me, after two hours of boring meetings, rituals and all that,

190
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:40,0000
when we were on one-on-one is, "Please, Yanis, don't mention again those bonds."

191
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:46,0000
And of course we had a dialectic of recognition there, right?

192
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:52,0000
And I said, "I will not do that if you don't shut down my banks."

193
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:56,0000
Cut again. And this is where my story ends.

194
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:02,0000
Two months later, I learned from within the European Central Bank,

195
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:06,0000
from a very high-ranking whistleblower, not Mario Draghi himself,

196
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:11,0000
but somebody very close, that the Greek prime minister, Mike Comrade and friend,

197
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:18,0000
Tsipras, had authorized a message to go through the deputy prime minister to Draghi,

198
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:23,0000
"Don't listen to Varoufakis. We're not going to let him do it."

199
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:28,0000
So there was a plan. It would have worked. There would have been some compromise.

200
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,0000
Of course there would have been a compromise.

201
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:35,0000
We would have to give stuff, but we would get effectively the only thing that I cared for.

202
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:43,0000
The only reason why I became part of this struggle was to get Greeks out of debtor's prison.

203
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,0000
That we would have achieved.

204
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:52,0000
And in the final analysis, so that was plan B, and there was a plan X.

205
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,0000
Plan X was the drachma.

206
00:16:54,000 --> 00:17:00,0000
Because yes, it is true that we would have lost not 30%, 20% of GDP again,

207
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:07,0000
but we would recover it relatively quickly within 18 to 20 months.

208
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:12,0000
Because in the end, at the moment, after all those years,

209
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:18,0000
our income now in Greece is lower than it was in 2015, and our debt is much, much higher,

210
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:22,0000
and we are a debt colony. We would have stopped being a debt colony.

211
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:26,0000
So, no regrets for anything.

212
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:30,0000
Except that I was a bit too lenient with the trica.

213
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:35,0000
Okay. Just two, and then we went to other topics.

214
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:39,0000
Two, or maybe even just one, how do you call it, sub-question.

215
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,0000
Okay.

216
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:44,0000
The obvious Stalinist one, who sees conspiracies, that's me.

217
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:49,0000
Why did Tsipras do it? What you said?

218
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:57,0000
Look, I have an ideological objection to giving a shit.

219
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:02,0000
This is between him and his maker, as the Christians would say.

220
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:06,0000
Why should I care about what he did? Why he did it?

221
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,0000
He did it. That's the only thing that matters. Why he did it?

222
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:13,0000
No, I didn't mean to dwell into his psychology, but was not...

223
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,0000
He did.

224
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:19,0000
No, what I meant is, was there pressure from some Greek banking circles?

225
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:23,0000
Of course there was pressure. I had pressure.

226
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:26,0000
Can you imagine the pressure? The pressure was unbelievable.

227
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:31,0000
Threats to our family, pressure galore.

228
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:37,0000
But why were we elected? We were elected knowing that that pressure would be there.

