278
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:01,0000
You would look at the bank and say, "Yeah, I haven't gone completely nuts."

279
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:05,0000
As if I'm going to say that. As if I'm going to say yes to that.

280
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:15,0000
So my line to Schauble was, "I'm not taking another credit card, pretending I'm going to pay you back on condition of destroying what is left of my people."

281
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:19,0000
And his argument was, "Okay, you're right. This doesn't work."

282
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:25,0000
He confessed that what he was proposing to us, what the troika was pushing down our throat, would never work.

283
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:28,0000
Lagarda confessed that to me too.

284
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:35,0000
Her argument was, "Yes, you're right, but you have to do what you're told, because otherwise you could build as a politician who's going to suffer."

285
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:42,0000
I thought, "Who gives a shit what my credibility as a politician suffers or doesn't suffer?"

286
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:52,0000
