00:35:57,000 --> 00:36:04,0000
Since 2008, the great financial crash, capitalism is on a drip feed.

454
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:10,0000
It's being kept alive through constant injections of money from the central banks.

455
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:12,0000
That has never happened before.

456
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:14,0000
It started in 2008.

457
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,0000
In 1929, it didn't happen.

458
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:22,0000
That's why all the banks closed down.

459
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:29,0000
So the banking system and the stock exchange had 12 years of getting used to, becoming addicted to,

460
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:35,0000
central bank money being pumped their way during difficult moments.

461
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:39,0000
So imagine you're a stock broker in London.

462
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:43,0000
You hear the news at 9 o'clock in the morning, minus 20%.

463
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:44,0000
Oh my God!

464
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,0000
You think that's the first thought.

465
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:52,0000
Then you think, ah, if I panicked, the guys and girls in the Bank of England, the central bank of England, are panicking.

466
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:55,0000
So what they're going to do is they're going to print even more billions

467
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:59,0000
and they will give it to me to play in the stock exchange.

468
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:01,0000
Bye.

