00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:09,0000
So the point I've been developing in my head, and we had a little discussion about this earlier

470
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:13,0000
because I was telling Slavoj that this will be my next book next year,

471
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:19,0000
it's my crazy theory that capitalism has already evolved out of itself.

472
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:23,0000
It has been transformed into another system.

473
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:28,0000
And the reason why I say that is because for me capitalism requires two things.

474
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:31,0000
Firstly, profit to drive it.

475
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:34,0000
It's like a petrol engine that needs petrol.

476
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:40,0000
Capitalism needs profit, private profit to drive it, capital accumulation as we Marxists used to say.

477
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:44,0000
And the other thing is that exploitation takes place in markets.

478
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:47,0000
That's the whole point about capitalism.

479
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:51,0000
In feudalism, there was no market exploitation.

480
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:58,0000
You had the peasants, they were growing rubbish, wheat and potatoes and cauliflower,

481
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:00,0000
I don't know what it is, that they were growing,

482
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:05,0000
and then the sheriff on behalf of the Lord would come and take half of it, or 60% of it.

483
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:10,0000
There was no market, it was just expropriation.

484
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:18,0000
It is with the enclosures and the eviction of the peasants who then become suppliers of labor at any price

485
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:24,0000
so that you have the creation of the working class and the labor market, because there was no labor market before that.

486
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:26,0000
So exploitation takes place through markets.

487
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:32,0000
Money markets, land markets, house markets, labor markets.

488
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:38,0000
But now, after 12 years of the 2008 crisis and beyond,

489
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:44,0000
we have the replacement of profit by central bank money,

490
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:48,0000
that is the new fuel of the system, of this exploitative system,

491
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:56,0000
and the steady encroachment into the space of markets of platforms.

492
00:38:56,000 --> 00:39:00,0000
Amazon. The moment you go into Amazon, or Facebook,

493
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:04,0000
the moment you enter Facebook, you're outside of capitalism, you're not in capitalism anymore.

