00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:24,0000
and some more people see your advertisements, right?

499
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:27,0000
You go in there to meet your friends.

500
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:32,0000
You want to advertise this evening.

501
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,0000
You go and pay money.

502
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:36,0000
One person owns the whole digital space.

503
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:39,0000
It is the equivalent of stepping outside in Ljubljana.

504
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:41,0000
Imagine, yeah, just science fiction for a moment.

505
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:45,0000
Imagine you step out in Ljubljana, on the streets of Ljubljana tonight,

506
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:50,0000
and you look around and you think, "Oh my God, all these buildings belong to one person."

507
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:56,0000
Everything that is traded in the shops that I see is controlled by one person,

508
00:39:56,000 --> 00:40:00,0000
who decides what prices are charged, what prices are not charged,

509
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:03,0000
who can trade, who can't trade, who can buy, who can't buy.

510
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:09,0000
And moreover, imagine that Ljubljana operated like Facebook does or Amazon does,

511
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:17,0000
whereby what your eyes see is determined by one person, by the algorithm of one person,

512
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:21,0000
who if he wants you not to see something, you will never see it in that digital space.

513
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:25,0000
This is not a market. This is a fief, a fiefdom.

514
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:28,0000
It's a digital fiefdom. It's a platform.

515
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:30,0000
Those platforms make a lot of money.

516
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:34,0000
But the rest of the economy, look at companies like Uber, for instance.

517
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,0000
They've never made a profit, ever.

518
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:40,0000
You have private equity. Have you heard of private equity?

519
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:42,0000
Do you know what private equity does?

520
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:48,0000
They go and they buy a company, let's say a company that provides health services.

521
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:51,0000
It's got doctors and nurses and stuff, private stuff.

522
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:55,0000
So they buy the hospital, they buy the company, and then they create two companies.

523
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:59,0000
One that owns the buildings and all the fixed assets,

524
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:02,0000
and the other that provides the services.

525
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:05,0000
And the second company sells the services to the first company.

526
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:08,0000
The first company has assets, buildings.

527
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:15,0000
So they go to the bank and they get a huge loan using as collateral the buildings of the first company.

528
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:17,0000
They take this money and they give it to themselves.

529
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:20,0000
They pay themselves. They give it to the shareholders.

530
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:22,0000
They pocket it. They put it in their money.

531
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:24,0000
Now, this whole company will never have a profit,

532
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:28,0000
because the second company will owe a huge quantity of money to the first company,

533
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:30,0000
and therefore they will never pay any tax,

534
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:32,0000
because if you have no profits, there is no tax.

535
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:36,0000
But the whole point about profitability is coming out.

536
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:41,0000
Very soon after that, this is an empty shell. This will go bankrupt. It will die.

537
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:45,0000
So platforms are expanding, even in health.

538
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:51,0000
