539
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:53,0000
Google is doing the same thing behind the scenes.

540
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:57,0000
By the way, DM25, our movement, is beginning a campaign on Monday in Britain

541
00:41:57,000 --> 00:42:04,0000
against the surreptitious privatization of the NHS by Big Tech.

542
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:06,0000
Close brackets.

543
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:11,0000
So you see, platforms are expanding. They are not markets, and markets are shrinking.

544
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:15,0000
And central bank money, sovereign money, that defends money,

545
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:17,0000
because they are defending the governments.

546
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:22,0000
They have no power, but their printing presses are keeping the system alive.

547
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:24,0000
I call this techno-fiddleism.

548
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:30,0000
And it's not just a question of curiosity about how the system works.

549
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:34,0000
It's also a question of what does this mean for daily lives?

550
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:36,0000
What does it mean for all of us?

551
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:38,0000
What does it mean for governments?

552
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:40,0000
I'll tell you what it means as an economist for a start.

553
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:44,0000
