554
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:50,0000
Because when platforms replace markets, and everything depends on the central bank money,

555
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:54,0000
if I make you the head of the European Central Bank tomorrow,

556
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:58,0000
you are the most slavish follower of the needs of business.

557
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:01,0000
You have no independence. You have no authority.

558
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:06,0000
Even if you want to reduce the amount of money, euros, that the ECB prints,

559
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:09,0000
you can't do it. The moment you do it, the whole thing will collapse.

560
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:14,0000
That's not central bank independence. That's dependence.

561
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:26,0000
It means that our governments are completely in the clasps of the interests of these large fiefdoms.

562
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:34,0000
And they have tiny degrees of freedom regarding fiscal policy, regarding redistribution of wealth,

563
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:41,0000
when all the wealth is encased and enclosed in the new fiefdoms.

564
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:48,0000
But also, and here is something that would be nice to talk a little bit more about,

565
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:51,0000
look, understand the capitalism.

566
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:57,0000
You have a working class which is exploited during the working time,

